Browser Host Examples
===============================================================================

Browser host examples live under `examples` and browser-oriented guide pages.

1. DOM demo
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```text
examples/browser-dom-demo/
```

This demo shows browser DOM host configuration, context binding, DOM reads, DOM writes, denied access, `mech serve`, and `bundle-web`.

Guide:

```text
/docs/guides/browser-dom-demo.mec
```

2. Static bundle
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Guide:

```text
/docs/guides/first-web-bundle.mec
```

3. Config-profile fixture
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```text
examples/browser-dom-resource.mcfg
examples/browser-dom-resource.mec
```

These files are retained because runtime config-profile tests include them directly. They are not the primary user-facing browser DOM example; use the full `browser-dom-demo` folder for that.
